Marines were among the 6,000 to lay wreaths in Arlington
Corporal De'Angello Robinson traveled seven hours by bus to lay a single wreath on the grave of a soldier whom he had never met.
For him and the other Marines who traveled from Camp Johnson in Jacksonville, North Carolina, to the National Cemetery in Arlington to decorate graves, the day was a tribute to the men and women in whose footsteps they have followed.
