The Manager Revolution or the End of Early Strategic Enlightenment?
If nothing changes in the leadership of large French companies, our struggle for the development of economic intelligence has been in vain...
For over a decade, the attitude of the management of large companies in terms of its employees, said the position of the company vis-à-vis the consumer before the marketing revolution: It is intended for staff to join "values" to impose the best, as it used to be on the consumer, products designed by the technicians at the factory.
